Selection sort is sorting algorithm in which the sorting is done by using nested loops the outer loop traverse through the array.
The outer loop element is replaced by the min element which is found out in the inner loop.The inner loop index starts from the index 
of the outer loop.

Code:

  class Solution {
    void selectionSort(int[] arr) {
        
        int n=arr.length;
        for(int i=0;i<n-1;i++)
        {
            int min=i;
            for(int j=i;j<n;j++)
            {
                if(arr[j]<arr[min])
                {
                    min=j;
                }
            }
            int temp=arr[i];
            arr[i]=arr[min];
            arr[min]=temp;
            
        }
    }
}

Time Complexity:O(n^2)
Space Complexity:O(1)